Read in data

outdoor <- read.csv("data/Hobo/temp_light_logger/Outdoor/OutdoorTank_20210620.csv", header=T, na.strings = "NA")[ ,2:4] # data from 20201221 onward
colnames(outdoor) <- c("Date.Time", "Temperature", "Light")
outdoor$Date.Time <- parse_date_time(outdoor$Date.Time, "mdyHMS", tz = "EST")

Plot data

# Plot temperature data
ggplot(outdoor, aes(x=Date.Time, y=Temperature)) +
  geom_line(size = 1)+
  #ylim(5,15)+
  ylab("Temperature C")
## Warning: Removed 5 row(s) containing missing values (geom_path).

ggsave("output/Hobo/temp_light_logger/OutdoorTank_HoboTemp.pdf", plot = last_plot(), width = 8, height = 4)

Plot June data (time when outdoor corals for AB were collected)

# Filter by June dates
june.temp <- outdoor %>% filter(Date.Time >= "2021-06-01 00:00:00")

# Plot June temperature data
ggplot(june.temp, aes(x=Date.Time, y=Temperature)) +
  geom_line(size = 5)+
  ylab("Temperature C")
## Warning: Removed 5 row(s) containing missing values (geom_path).
